      "source": [
        "** * NOTE: ALL THE COMMANDS FOR PLOTTING A FIGURE SHOULD ALL GO IN THE SAME CELL. SEPARATING THEM OUT INTO MULTIPLE CELLS MAY CAUSE NOTHING TO SHOW UP. * **\n",
        "\n",
        "# Exercises\n",
        "\n",
        "Follow the instructions to recreate the plots using this data:\n",
        "\n",
        "## Data"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 1,
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "EZtaMMLbERAv"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "x = np.arange(0,100)\n",
        "y = x*2\n",
        "z = x**2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F5S9BABTERAz"
      },
      "source": [
        "** Import matplotlib.pyplot as plt and set %matplotlib inline if you are using the jupyter notebook. What command do you use if you aren't using the jupyter notebook?**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "Im51BnFRERA1"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "%matplotlib inline\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-zPHNNtLERA2"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Exercise 1\n",
        "\n",
        "** Follow along with these steps: **\n",
        "* ** Create a figure object called fig using plt.figure() **\n",
        "* ** Use add_axes to add an axis to the figure canvas at [0,0,1,1]. Call this new axis ax. **\n",
        "* ** Plot (x,y) on that axes and set the labels and titles to match the plot below:**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 383
        },
        "id": "wrqm4rapERA3",
        "outputId": "c7a60d30-3652-403d-d7ec-e6799317ac74"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'title')"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 3
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {
            "needs_background": "light"
          }
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "Fig_1 = plt.figure()\n",
        "ax = Fig_1.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",
        "ax.plot(x,y)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('x')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('y')\n",
        "ax.set_title('title')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xibjShpEERA6"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Exercise 2\n",
        "** Create a figure object and put two axes on it, ax1 and ax2. Located at [0,0,1,1] and [0.2,0.5,.2,.2] respectively.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 4,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 340
        },
        "id": "6-yxv2-UERA8",
        "outputId": "1a405301-c590-4941-9e75-d99d36e92869"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {
            "needs_background": "light"
          }
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "Fig_2 = plt.figure()\n",
        "axis1 = Fig_2.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",
        "axis2 = Fig_2.add_axes([0.2,0.5,0.2,0.2])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pIR1lh1RERA_"
      },
      "source": [
        "** Now plot (x,y) on both axes. And call your figure object to show it.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 5,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 350
        },
        "id": "bYW5XyGEERBC",
        "outputId": "a89ad6f4-14d0-48f1-a180-412be6555963"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 5
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "axis1.plot(x,y)\n",
        "axis1.set_xlabel('x')\n",
        "axis1.set_ylabel('y')\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "axis2.plot(x,y)\n",
        "axis2.set_xlabel('x')\n",
        "axis2.set_ylabel('y')\n",
        "\n",
        "Fig_2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",

        "id": "q4oJ950HERBE"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Exercise 3\n",
        "\n",
        "** Create the plot below by adding two axes to a figure object at [0,0,1,1] and [0.2,0.5,.4,.4]**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 6,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 340
        },
        "id": "2d-pmJ9wERBF",
        "outputId": "9d792c1e-9950-43fc-a5bb-ffbcde096617"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {
            "needs_background": "light"
          }
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "Fig_3 = plt.figure()\n",
        "axis1 = Fig_3.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",
        "axis2 = Fig_3.add_axes([0.2,0.5,0.4,0.4])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4aQdqud8ERBH"
      },
      "source": [
        "** Now use x,y, and z arrays to recreate the plot below. Notice the xlimits and y limits on the inserted plot:**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 7,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 350
        },
        "id": "lzA8WTx_ERBI",
        "outputId": "09da945e-4960-4377-8292-ec13fe93a3a5"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 7
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "axis1.plot(x,z)\n",
        "axis1.set_xlabel('X')\n",
        "axis1.set_ylabel('Z')\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "axis2.plot(x,y)\n",
        "axis2.set_xlabel('X')\n",
        "axis2.set_ylabel('Y')\n",
        "\n",
        "axis2.set_title('zoom')\n",
        "\n",
        "axis2.set_xlim(20,22)\n",
        "axis2.set_ylim(30,50)\n",
        "\n",
        "Fig_3"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",

      },
      "source": [

        "\n",
        "** Use plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2) to create the plot below.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 8,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 269
        },

        "outputId": "ac10e5f6-2db1-4bb3-911d-c7e231ba8445"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {
            "needs_background": "light"
          }
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "Fig_1, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2)"
      ]

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Vx_JVcqlERBM"
      },
      "source": [
        "** Now plot (x,y) and (x,z) on the axes. Play around with the linewidth and style**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 9,
      "metadata": {

      "source": [

        "axes[1].plot(x,z, color = \"cyan\" , ls = 'dashed')\n",

        "Fig_1\n"
